<item>
            <title>[JDK-8307156] native_thread not protected by TLH</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8307156</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;br/&gt;
In jfrJavaSupport.cpp:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;static JavaThread* get_native(jobject thread) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;ThreadsListHandle tlh;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;JavaThread* native_thread = NULL;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(void)tlh.cv_internal_thread_to_JavaThread(thread, &amp;amp;native_thread, NULL);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;return native_thread;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This code seems to return a native thread after the TLH that protects it returns so appears unsafe.</description>
